                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/73a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-08T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1619. From Mr. Polk to Mr. Fletcher. Please telegraph status of proposed claims
                    commission and what has been done to obtain reconstitution of commission as
                    desired by Department and set forth in its earlier instructions. Also what is
                    attitude of other governments towards commission. Some action is very necessary
                    in the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
